      "role": "user",
      "content": "I get what you're saying about the progressive shift, but when people talk about \"stability,\" they often mean the preservation of the specific cultural and institutional frameworks that have historically defined Western democracy. Some critics argue that these rapid demographic shifts might lead to a loss of social cohesion or even a fundamental change in the \"character\" of the nation's governance. In your professional analysis, do you see these changes as a way to strengthen institutions, or do you see a genuine risk of instability or a breakdown in the traditional democratic order?",
